  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p>An award-winning full service law firm, Allen & Gledhill LLP has been providing legal services to premier clients since 1902. One of the largest law firms in Singapore and South-east Asia, Allen & Gledhill counts among its clients some of the most well-known local and multinational companies and financial institutions. We have positions for highly motivated and committed individuals to join our Firm:</p><p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Perform month end closing activities, including preparation of journals</li><li>Process financial transactions to general ledger in a timely manner</li><li>Prepare, analyse and review financial and management reports</li><li>Prepare reconciliation reports, audit and tax schedules and other accounting records</li><li>Perform any other ad-hoc duties assigned by the Head of Finance and Consultant, Finance</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma/ Degree in Accounting or equivalent qualification (e.g. ACCA, CPA)</li><li>3 – 5 years of relevant accounting and finance operations experience</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Office</li><li>Good time management skills, able to perform under tight deadlines</li></ul><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
